Headline: Lionel Messi’s global tour with Inter Miami has been very messy and a PR nightmare
Content: It’s all been very messy. We’re talking about Lionel Messi and Inter Miami’s global tour of exhibition games where the main show has been Argentina’s 2022 World Cup-winning captain.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s first contract with Barcelona was signed on a napkin. Now it’s up for auction
Content: Lionel Messi’s record-breaking career with Barcelona started with a contract written on a napkin. It’s up for auction with a starting price of 300,000 pounds.

Headline: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami show off new jersey, help christen a new ship
Content: Lionel Messi showed off a new jersey, then helped christen a new ship. Inter Miami celebrated its partnership with cruise line Royal Caribbean International on Tuesday by sending Messi and his teammates to the Port of Miami, where they took part in the traditional naming of a new ship — the Icon of

Headline: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami are in Saudi Arabia to continue their around-the-world preseason tour
Content: Inter Miami played six preseason matches last season. Most were behind closed doors with few people watching, all took place in Florida and the biggest news probably came when some fans prematurely set off fireworks and got ejected from the exhibition-season opener.

Headline: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami begin their preseason with a 0-0 draw against El Salvador
Content: Four days after being named FIFA’s best men’s player, Lionel Messi began the preseason with Inter Miami of Major League Soccer, which played to a scoreless draw with the El Salvador national team in an exhibition.

Headline: Lionel Messi and the World Cup have left Qatar with a richer sports legacy
Content: Reminders of Lionel Messi and the 2022 World Cup are not hard to find in Qatar. “Last chance” tournament souvenirs greet visitors on arrival at Doha’s Hamad International Airport.

Headline: Lionel Messi lit up the 2022 World Cup in Qatar. Now it is Akram Afif’s turn to shine at Asian Cup
Content: Lionel Messi lit up the 2022 World Cup in Qatar. Now it is Akram Afif’s turn to shine. It is just over a year on from Messi’s triumph and Qatar is hosting another major tournament.

Headline: Messi and Inter Miami close messy preseason with 1-1 draw against Newell’s Old Boys
Content: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami brought their tumultuous Major League Soccer preseason to a close with a 1-1 draw against Messi’s boyhood club, Newell’s Old Boys.

Headline: Lionel Messi wasn’t seen at MLS media day. Doesn’t matter, since everyone talked about him
Content: Lionel Messi was not visible at Major League Soccer’s annual media day on Thursday. His shadow was. Messi is entering his first full season with Inter Miami, which creates an obvious storyline that seems to be on everyone’s mind as MLS teams enter their preseason training camps.

Headline: Luis Suárez signs with Inter Miami, reunites with former Barcelona teammate Lionel Messi
Content: The long-awaited reunion of Luis Suárez and Lionel Messi is now a reality, after the Uruguayan striker signed with Inter Miami on Friday for the 2024 season.

Headline: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami add Japan stop to preseason tour
Content: The preseason tour for Lionel Messi and Inter Miami keeps growing, with the team revealing that a stop in Japan has now been added to the schedule.

Headline: Furor over Messi no-show in Hong Kong game deepens with Argentina’s tour of China canceled
Content: The fallout from Lionel Messi’s failure to play in a club exhibition match in Hong Kong has spread with both of Argentina’s friendly matches as part of a tour of mainland China next month canceled by local football authorities.

Headline: After public anger over Messi’s absence in Hong Kong game, organizer withdraws application for funds
Content: The organizer of a soccer match featuring Inter Miami in Hong Kong was dealing with backlash from both angry fans and the government after widespread disappointment that Lionel Messi didn’t play in the game.

Headline: Messi and Inter Miami lose to Saudi Arabian team Al-Hilal
Content: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami have kicked off their tour of Saudi Arabia by losing to Al-Hilal 4-3. The Major League Soccer team is playing two games in the oil-rich kingdom as part of its offseason preparations but even Messi could not inspire it to victory in Riyadh.

Headline: Messi to make his Super Bowl debut, set to appear in Michelob Ultra ad
Content: Lionel Messi has won futbol’s biggest prize. He’ll now be part of American football’s biggest day. The Inter Miami star, World Cup champion and global soccer icon will headline a Super Bowl ad for Michelob Ultra, the brand has announced.

Headline: Today in Sports - 16-year old Lionel Messi makes his official debut for FC Barcelona
Content: Today in Sports, November 16 - 16-year old Lionel Messi makes his official debut for FC Barcelona

Headline: Messi vs. Mbappé on the global stage again? Argentina has qualified for the Paris Olympics
Content: The stars are starting to align for another Lionel Messi vs. Kylian Mbappé showdown on a global soccer stage to follow their epic World Cup final in 2022.

Headline: Messi plays and has chances but Vissel Kobe beats Inter Miami 4-3 on penalties in a friendly
Content: After leaving fans disappointed in Hong Kong, Lionel Messi put in a 30-minute appearance in Tokyo in Inter Miami’s latest exhibition match in Asia.

Headline: Messi’s Inter Miami routed 6-0 by Al-Nassr in a friendly as Ronaldo watches from stands
Content: What was billed as a potential final meeting between longtime rivals Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo didn’t materialize, but there was no doubt which of the superstars enjoyed Al-Nassr’s 6-0 rout of Inter Miami more.

Headline: Lionel Messi is a finalist for the MLS Newcomer of the Year award
Content: Lionel Messi is a finalist for the MLS Newcomer of the Year award. The league announced the finalists for its season awards on Thursday.

Headline: Lionel Messi draws Brazilian fans to what could be the Argentine great’s last match in Rio
Content: Many Brazilians have become fans of Lionel Messi in recent years. And many of them will be going to the Maracana Stadium to watch the World Cup champions take on their own national team in a qualifying match.

Headline: Busy 2024 looms for Lionel Messi and Inter Miami, and club is figuring out how to make it work
Content: Inter Miami is putting together its preseason schedule, one that will likely have somewhere between four and six games early next year.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s Argentina to play Nigeria and Ivory Coast in March exhibitions during China tour
Content: Argentina will play exhibition games against Nigeria and Ivory Coast in China next month, making it likely Lionel Messi will miss Inter Miami’s Major League Soccer game at the New York Red Bulls on March 23.

Headline: Anger over Messi’s absence in Hong Kong game spreads: Argentina friendly in mainland China canceled
Content: An Argentina soccer friendly in China next month has been canceled in more fallout from Lionel Messi failing to play in a club exhibition match in Hong Kong.

Headline: Messi says he feels much better and hopes to play in Tokyo after a PR disaster in Hong Kong
Content: Look for Lionel Messi to play in Tokyo on Wednesday when Inter Miami faces Japanese club Vissel Kobe in a friendly.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s 8th Ballon D’Or trophy celebrated by Inter Miami in exhibition match
Content: Lionel Messi held the Ballon D’Or over his head as fireworks lit up the sky to bring a pregame ceremony to a close.

Headline: Lionel Messi in starting lineup for Inter Miami in MLS season finale at Charlotte
Content: Lionel Messi is in the starting lineup for Inter Miami in its MLS season finale against FC Charlotte.

Headline: Suárez’s training alongside Messi, Busquets and Alba with Inter Miami officially underway
Content: Lionel Messi, Luis Suárez, Sergio Busquets and Jordi Alba were all sitting together and smiling after a training session. This wasn’t Barcelona in 2014.

Headline: Today in Sports - 17-year old Lionel Messi makes his league debut for FC Barcelona
Content: Today in Sports, October 16 - 17-year old Lionel Messi makes his league debut for FC Barcelona

Headline: Lionel Messi may play Saturday, Inter Miami hints in social media post
Content: Lionel Messi’s absence from Inter Miami’s lineup may be over. The team used social media on Friday to post “Nos vemos mañana” with a photo of the seven-time Ballon d’Or winner.

Headline: Sporting KC moves match against Lionel Messi’s Inter Miami to Chiefs’ Arrowhead Stadium
Content: Sporting Kansas City moved its April 13 Major League Soccer home game against Lionel Messi’s Inter Miami to Arrowhead Stadium from the team’s Children’s Mercy Park.

Headline: Lionel Messi and Luis Suárez face off in World Cup qualifying. Brazil could field teenager Endrick
Content: Lionel Messi and Luiz Suárez will renew their on-the-field rivalry on Thursday in World Cup qualifying. Messi appears to have recovered from a muscle injury in his leg.

Headline: Lionel Messi remains a doubtful starter for Argentina. Neymar under fire in Brazil
Content: Lionel Messi’s involvement in a 1-0 win over Paraguay last week doesn’t necessarily mean he’ll be fit for Argentina’s next game in World Cup qualifying against Peru.

Headline: Messi has 3 shots on goal, exits in 2nd half in Inter Miami’s 1-0 loss to FC Dallas in MLS friendly
Content: Lionel Messi had three shots on goal before exiting early in the second half in Inter Miami’s 1-0 loss to FC Dallas in an MLS preseason game at the Cotton Bowl.

Headline: Fans unhappy at not seeing injured Messi play as Inter Miami cruises past Hong Kong XI 4-1
Content: Hong Kong soccer fans and government have expressed their disappointment as Lionel Messi stayed on the bench for the full 90 minutes while Inter Miami defeated a Hong Kong XI 4-1 in the latest stop on the MLS team’s preseason Asian tour.

Headline: Pep Guardiola says Lionel Messi and Erling Haaland both deserve to win Ballon d’Or
Content: Pep Guardiola says Lionel Messi and Erling Haaland both deserve to win this year’s Ballon d’Or award for the world’s best soccer player.

Headline: Today in Sports - Lionel Messi becomes the UEFA Champions League all-time scorer
Content: Today in Sports, November 25 - Lionel Messi becomes the UEFA Champions League all-time scorer

Headline: Messi edges Haaland in tiebreaker for FIFA’s best men’s player award. Bonmatí takes women’s prize
Content: Lionel Messi has landed another prestigious award in soccer but the Argentina star needed a tiebreaker with Erling Haaland to win FIFA’s best men’s player prize on Monday.

Headline: Lionel Messi misses 2nd match this week, doesn’t dress for Miami at Atlanta
Content: Inter Miami star Lionel Messi did not dress for a match at Atlanta United, the second match he missed this week.

Headline: Lionel Messi misses Inter Miami’s game at Chicago because of scar tissue ailment
Content: Lionel Messi wasn’t in Chicago with Inter Miami on Wednesday night for a game against the Fire, missing his fifth match in the last six with the MLS club.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s status is unclear, and the Chicago Fire want to lure fans to Soldier Field anyway
Content: Lionel Messi was on the practice field with Inter Miami on Tuesday, though it remains unclear when or if the seven-time Ballon d’Or winner will play with the Major League Soccer team again this season.

Headline: Messi’s Miami opens MLS on Feb. 21. Star could miss at least 6 matches while with Argentina
Content: Lionel Messi’s first full season with Major League Soccer’s Inter Miami starts Feb. 21 at home against Real Salt Lake in a matchup three days ahead of other openers, and Messi could miss at least six games while with Argentina’s national team.

Headline: Without Lionel Messi, Inter Miami loses 2-1 to Houston in US Open Cup final
Content: Lionel Messi was not on Inter Miami’s roster for the U.S. Open Cup final against Houston on Wednesday night, marking the fourth match for club and country that he’s missed in recent weeks while dealing with some sort of leg issue.

Headline: Lionel Messi misses another Inter Miami match with leg injury. His team rallies, ties NYCFC 1-1
Content: The Lionel Messi injury mystery continues. Messi was ruled out for Inter Miami’s match against New York City FC on Saturday night.

Headline: Lionel Messi will miss another game for Inter Miami after leaving Toronto match early
Content: Lionel Messi returned to Inter Miami’s lineup on Wednesday night. It was a short-lived comeback and he will now miss at least one more match.

Headline: Messi vs. Ronaldo rivalry could be rekindled in Saudi Arabia tournament
Content: Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo could resume their longstanding rivalry in a tournament being staged in Saudi Arabia in February.

Headline: Lionel Messi and two more MLS players called up by Argentina for World Cup qualifying
Content: Lionel Messi was among three MLS-based players to be called up by Argentina on Thursday for the opening rounds of South American World Cup qualifying.

Headline: MLS commissioner says 2023 was undeniably the Year of Messi but season also had other high points
Content: The 2023 Major League Soccer season was undeniably the year of Lionel Messi. The World Cup champion and eight-time Ballon d’Or winner arrived at Inter Miami this summer and changed the league.

Headline: Lionel Messi scores 2 in Argentina’s World Cup qualifying win over Peru; Brazil’s Neymar injured
Content: Lionel Messi scored twice in Argentina’s 2-0 win at Peru in a World Cup qualifier, playing the entire match for his national team.

Headline: Lionel Messi plays one half in Argentina’s 1-0 World Cup qualifying win; Brazil and Venezuela draw
Content: Lionel Messi hit a post twice after he came off the bench but struggled to deliver a strong performance following his return from injury.

Headline: Scoreless for first time in the Lionel Messi era, Inter Miami ties Nashville 0-0
Content: Inter Miami failed to score for the first time since Lionel Messi joined the team, playing a scoreless draw with Nashville on Wednesday night.

Headline: Ronaldo to miss reunion with Messi after being ruled out of Al-Nassr’s friendly with Inter Miami
Content: Cristiano Ronaldo will miss the chance of a much anticipated reunion with Lionel Messi because of an injury.

Headline: Set of 6 Messi World Cup shirts sells for $7.8 million at auction in New York
Content: Six jerseys worn by soccer superstar Lionel Messi during Argentina’s winning run at last year’s World Cup have sold for $7.8 million.

Headline: Columbus Crew ask minimum $421 for individual tickets vs. Messi and Miami next season
Content: The Columbus Crew are asking a minimum $421 list price for individual tickets for next season’s Major League Soccer home game against Inter Miami and Lionel Messi.

Headline: Lionel Messi makes MLS debut, enters in 60th minute for Miami against New York Red Bulls
Content: Lionel Messi made his Major League Soccer debut, entering in the 60th minute of Inter Miami’s match at the New York Red Bulls.

Headline: Mbappé has reached 300 career goals faster than Messi or Ronaldo. His France elders are impressed.
Content: Kylian Mbappé has scored 300 career goals faster than Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi. His France elders have nothing but admiration.

Headline: Lionel Messi scores again, Inter Miami tops Philadelphia 4-1 to make Leagues Cup final
Content: Lionel Messi keeps scoring goals, and Inter Miami keeps winning games. Messi ripped a shot from 30 yards past three Philadelphia defenders in the 20th minute, and Miami beat the Philadelphia Union 4-1 to reach the Leagues Cup final.

Headline: Messi’s trip to China for a pair of Inter Miami exhibition games called off
Content: Eight-time Ballon d’Or winner Lionel Messi evidently won’t be playing in China this month after all.

Headline: Inter Miami loses attacker Facundo Farías for the season with a torn ACL
Content: Inter Miami attacker Facundo Farías has a torn ACL in his left knee and will miss the entire season. The team made the announcement on Saturday.

Headline: Messi’s 1st year with Inter Miami brings a trophy and shows what can happen in Year 2
Content: Lionel Messi’s first season with Inter Miami is complete. And now he’s the favorite to win the Ballon d’Or trophy that will be presented in Paris on Monday.

Headline: Lionel Messi makes it official by signing with Inter Miami and Major League Soccer
Content: Lionel Messi has finalized his deal to join Major League Soccer. And after years of planning and pursuing, Inter Miami has landed a global icon.

Headline: Messi seeks 1st goal against Brazil in World Cup qualifying, hosts try to avert crisis in Rio
Content: Lionel Messi has few barriers yet to break in soccer. One of them will be in reach Tuesday, when Argentina visits Brazil in a South American World Cup qualifying match.

Headline: Messi’s Argentina beats Brazil in a World Cup qualifying game delayed by crowd violence
Content: Many fans went to the Maracana Stadium to watch Lionel Messi in his likely last match in Brazil, a superclasico in World Cup qualifying against the hosts.

Headline: Lionel Messi picked for Argentina squad for upcoming World Cup qualifying matches
Content: Lionel Messi has been picked for Argentina’s next two World Cup qualifying matches despite muscular pains that have kept him off the field for two weeks.

Headline: Celebrities and fans travel from all over to watch Lionel Messi’s MLS debut with Inter Miami
Content: Fans from all over the world bounced around the outskirts of DRV PNK Stadium ahead of Lionel Messi’s MLS debut with Inter Miami. Dozens stood in line for team gear.

Headline: Messi sits out Argentina’s World Cup qualifying match at Bolivia
Content: Lionel Messi will sit out Argentina’s World Cup qualifying match in Bolivia. The 36-year-old Inter Miami star was neither in the starting lineup for the World Cup champions nor on the bench.

Headline: Jordi Alba to reunite with Lionel Messi, Sergio Busquets at Inter Miami
Content: Veteran defender Jordi Alba is set to join former FC Barcelona teammates Lionel Messi and Sergio Busquets in Miami.

Headline: Messi wins record-extending 8th Ballon d’Or, Bonmati takes women’s award
Content: Lionel Messi has won a record-extending eighth Ballon d’Or in Paris. The Argentine great fulfilled his life’s ambition by leading his country to the World Cup title in Qatar last year to win the one major trophy that eluded him in his incredible career.

Headline: Lionel Messi scores a sensational game-winning goal on a free kick in his Inter Miami debut
Content: Lionel Messi scored a dramatic, game-winning goal in his debut with Inter Miami. Messi’s free kick in stoppage time from about 25 yards gave his team a 2-1 victory.

Headline: Messi to travel with Argentina but uncertain for game against Bolivia in World Cup qualifying
Content: Lionel Messi will travel with the Argentina squad to Bolivia for its South American World Cup qualifier on Tuesday but his presence on the field remains uncertain.

Headline: Lionel Messi earns $20.4 million under contract with Major League Soccer’s Inter Miami
Content: Lionel Messi’s annualized compensation from his Major League Soccer contract with Inter Miami is just over $20.4 million.

Headline: Messi’s status for US Open Cup final on Wednesday remains unclear
Content: Lionel Messi’s status remains unclear for Inter Miami’s U.S. Open Cup final match against Houston on Wednesday night.

Headline: Messi’s Ballon d’Or will be celebrated by Inter Miami in exhibition vs. NYCFC on Nov. 10
Content: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami will play an exhibition match on Nov. 10 to celebrate him winning his eighth Ballon d’Or.

Headline: Lionel Messi is expected to make his Inter Miami debut July 21
Content: Lionel Messi is expected to make his Major League Soccer debut with Inter Miami at a July 21 home game, the team confirmed Tuesday.

Headline: Messi World Cup shirts will be auctioned. Sotheby’s thinks they could fetch record over $10 million
Content: Sotheby’s is set to auction off six shirts worn by Lionel Messi during Argentina’s winning run at last year’s soccer World Cup in Qatar.

Headline: Messi plays entire game for Inter Miami in a 1-0 loss as Charlotte qualifies for the MLS playoffs
Content: Lionel Messi played the entire game on artificial turf in Inter Miami’s season finale, and Charlotte qualified for the MLS playoffs with a 1-0 victory on Saturday night.

Headline: Post-World Cup, Qatar is pressing ahead with labor reforms but concerns for migrant workers remain
Content: The enduring image of the 2022 World Cup was Lionel Messi holding aloft soccer’s biggest prize in Qatar’s spectacular Lusail Stadium.

Headline: Lionel Messi takes to the practice field for 1st time since signing with Inter Miami
Content: Lionel Messi jogged a lap with his new teammates, took part in a warmup drill of players making short passes in a tight circle and before long tapped his left foot at a ball that wound up in the back of an open net.

Headline: Lionel Messi shines again in first Inter Miami start, scores twice in 4-0 win over Atlanta
Content: Lionel Messi scored twice and added an assist in his first start for Inter Miami, leading his new club to a 4-0 win over Atlanta United in the Leagues Cup.

Headline: Messi out for Inter Miami’s home finale, says he wants to play Saturday at Charlotte
Content: Lionel Messi says he will play in Inter Miami’s season finale on Saturday, although the club hasn’t confirmed that is the actual plan.

Headline: Messi and Miami miss MLS playoffs, eliminated with 1-0 loss to Cincinnati
Content: Lionel Messi’s first season in Major League Soccer will end without a trip to the playoffs following Inter Miami’s 1-0 loss to FC Cincinnati.

Headline: Neymar’s ACL injury compounds troubled start to his next chapter as Ronaldo and Messi thrive
Content: Neymar left the soccer field in tears after yet another injury in what has become an all-too familiar sight.

Headline: Messi, Inter Miami schedule match in Hong Kong on Feb. 4
Content: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami are headed to Hong Kong. The club revealed plans Thursday for a Feb. 4 match there on its first international tour, part of its preseason before the 2024 Major League Soccer campaign.

Headline: Lionel Messi bids farewell to Paris amid boos
Content: Lionel Messi didn’t care about the boos in his final game for Paris Saint-Germain as the French league champion lost to Clermont 3-2.

Headline: Coach confirms Lionel Messi’s last match for PSG this weekend
Content: Lionel Messi is leaving Paris Saint-Germain at the end of the season after two years at the club. PSG coach Christophe Galtier says ahead of their game against Clermont on Saturday that it will be Messi’s last match at the Parc des Princes.

Headline: The world’s largest cruise ship has 20 decks, 7 pools and would cover almost 4 city blocks
Content: The world’s largest cruise ship is set to begin its maiden voyage from the Port of Miami. Royal Caribbean’s Icon of the Seas is leaving South Florida on Saturday for its first seven-day island-hopping voyage through the tropics.

Headline: Messi’s Argentina loses 1st match since World Cup title, falling to Uruguay; Colombia beats Brazil
Content: Lionel Messi could not help Argentina keep its unbeaten streak since its World Cup title. Uruguay beat Argentina 2-0 at La Bombonera Stadium in Buenos Aires on Thursday in a World Cup qualifying match.

Headline: Ronaldo walks off to chants of ‘Messi! Messi!’ as his team loses 3-0 in Riyadh derby
Content: Cristiano Ronaldo walked off the field with the gleeful chants of “Messi! Messi!” ringing in his ears from delighted Al-Hilal fans.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s title in Qatar set to inspire Argentina at Women’s World Cup
Content: Argentina’s team will draw inspiration from Lionel Messi’s achievement in Qatar in its quest to reach the knockout stage of the Women’s World Cup for the first time.

Headline: Ticket sales and anticipation are high ahead of Lionel Messi’s arrival at Inter Miami
Content: Lionel Messi announced that he was joining Inter Miami in a move that stunned the soccer world and will bring the sport’s biggest face to the United States and Miami, where enthusiasm for the sport has been growing over the years.

Headline: Atlanta United turns up the offense, capitalizes on Messi’s absence, to beat Inter Miami 5-2
Content: Atlanta United took the lead with a three-goal spree late in the first half and beat Inter Miami, playing without star Lionel Messi, 5-2.

Headline: The next chapter of Lionel Messi’s career begins Friday at 18,000-seat DRV PNK Stadium
Content: Lionel Messi will make his Inter Miami debut Friday at DRV PNK Stadium, ushering in the next chapter of his career.

Headline: Messi skips Argentina’s last practice before World Cup qualifier in Bolivia
Content: Lionel Messi has skipped Argentina’s last practice session before its World Cup qualifying match in Bolivia.

Headline: Messi Mania has grabbed hold in Major League Soccer, but will it be a long-lasting boost?
Content: Lionel Messi’s arrival in the United States has boosted his team and Major League Soccer. No. 10 jerseys have been flying off the shelves, ticket prices have at times reached unheard-of levels and Inter Miami’s games have been selling out, even on the road.

Headline: No Messi, no problem: Campana scores twice as Inter Miami beats Sporting KC
Content: With Lionel Messi out of the lineup to play in a pair of World Cup qualifiers for reigning champion Argentina, Inter Miami got two goals from Leonardo Campana to beat Sporting Kansas City 3-2.

Headline: Messi, Mbappé or Haaland to be FIFA best player in 2023. Women’s best is Bonmatí, Hermoso or Caicedo
Content: The FIFA best men’s player award for 2023 will be another contest between Lionel Messi, Kylian Mbappé and Erling Haaland.

Headline: Lionel Messi’s father says no deal agreed with a future club
Content: Speculation over Lionel Messi’s potential next destination is turning into a media frenzy but his father has intervened to say no deal has been agreed over a move to Saudi Arabia or return to Barcelona.

Headline: Messi violates MLS media rules by not speaking with reporters after debut
Content: Lionel Messi did not speak with reporters after his Major League Soccer debut, a violation of the league’s media rules.

Headline: Messi’s Inter Miami team strikes 2-game deal to play in China in November
Content: Lionel Messi is evidently going back to China, after Inter Miami took advantage of not making the Major League Soccer playoffs by signing a deal to play two exhibitions there next month.

Headline: Messi a doubtful starter for Argentina; Vinicius back with Brazil for World Cup qualifying
Content: Lionel Messi is again a doubtful starter for Argentina in the next World Cup qualifying match against Paraguay.

Headline: Lionel Messi scores, gets hugged by a fan during Argentina’s 2-0 win over Australia
Content: Lionel Messi got hugged by a fan who ran onto the field wearing a No. 10 Argentina shirt during a 2-0 friendly win over Australia in which the World Cup champion scored the fastest goal of his career.

Headline: PSG to shift focus following likely exit of Lionel Messi
Content: Lionel Messi’s impending exit from Paris Saint-Germain could mark the beginning of the end of the French soccer club’s era of excess.

Headline: AP Source: Lionel Messi set to leave PSG at end of season
Content: Lionel Messi is set to leave Paris Saint-Germain when his contract expires at the end of the season after two years with the French soccer team a person with knowledge of the situation told The Associated Press.

Headline: Lionel Messi introduced by Inter Miami and Major League Soccer
Content: Lionel Messi has met his new fans at Inter Miami. An event billed as “The Unveil” was Sunday night at the team’s stadium in Fort Lauderdale.

Headline: Messi’s MLS regular-season debut delayed, likely until Aug. 26
Content: Major League Soccer fans will have to wait a little longer for Lionel Messi’s first regular-season match with Inter Miami.

Headline: South Florida: Heat and Panthers play for titles, plus arrival of soccer star Lionel Messi
Content: South Florida has suddenly become the center of the sports universe. The Miami Heat are in the NBA Finals, the Florida Panthers are in the NHL’s Stanley Cup Final and the area is hosting championship-series games an unprecedented four nights in a row.

Headline: Lionel Messi picks MLS’s Inter Miami in a move that stuns soccer after exit from Paris Saint-Germain
Content: Lionel Messi says he is coming to Inter Miami and joining Major League Soccer. After months of speculation, Messi announced his decision to join a Miami franchise that has been led by another global soccer icon in David Beckham since its inception but has yet to make any real splashes on the field.

Headline: Argentina eyes Di Maria and Brazil tests Jesus ahead of World Cup qualifying clash
Content: Argentina and Brazil tested new options up front on Saturday for their World Cup qualifying match next week.

Headline: Messi has 2 assists in front of star-studded crowd in Los Angeles as Inter Miami beats LAFC 3-1
Content: Lionel Messi had two assists in front of a star-studded crowd as Inter Miami defeated Los Angeles Football Club 3-1.

Headline: Messi scores in regulation, penalties to lead Inter Miami past Nashville in Leagues Cup final
Content: Lionel Messi scored early in regulation and converted the first shot in penalty kicks as Inter Miami beat Nashville SC 10-9 on penalties in the Leagues Cup final on Saturday night.

Headline: MATCHDAY: Ronaldo reflects on Messi rivalry ahead of playing for Portugal in Euro 2024 qualifying
Content: Cristiano Ronaldo has been in reflective mood as he brings up 20 years in Portugal’s national team. Ronaldo says he and great rival Lionel Messi “changed the history of soccer” and that he still wants to raise the bar at the age of 38.

Headline: Messi is a doubtful starter for Argentina’s World Cup qualifying game in Bolivia
Content: All 10 national teams in South America will play their second World Cup qualifying games on Tuesday.

Headline: Inter Miami to play 2 matches in Saudi Arabia. Messi vs. Ronaldo will happen Feb. 1
Content: Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo will meet in Saudi Arabia after all. Inter Miami confirmed Monday that it will take part in the Riyadh Season Cup, something that was announced by Saudi officials on Nov. 21.

Headline: Messi and Bonmati lead Ballon d’Or nominee lists, Ronaldo misses cut
Content: Seven-time Ballon d’Or winner Lionel Messi is back in contention for the prestigious award a year after being omitted from the nomination list which this time doesn’t include longtime rival Cristiano Ronaldo.

Headline: Shohei Ohtani joins big-money club with massive contract with Los Angeles Dodgers
Content: Shohei Ohtani, Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo, Patrick Mahomes and Mike Trout are among the world’s top athletes, each with a long list of epic accomplishments.

Headline: Messi scores dazzling goal in MLS debut, leads Miami over New York Red Bulls
Content: Lionel Messi scored a dazzling goal in the 89th minute of his Major League Soccer debut, helping Inter Miami beat the New York Red Bulls 2-0 and end an 11-match league winless streak.

Headline: Inter Miami confirms hiring of Tata Martino, reuniting him with Lionel Messi
Content: Inter Miami confirmed the hiring of Gerardo “Tata” Martino as coach on Wednesday, setting the stage for him to be reunited with Lionel Messi next month.

Headline: Messi scores again, Inter Miami tops Charlotte 4-0 to make Leagues Cup semifinals
Content: Lionel Messi’s goalscoring streak lives on, as does Inter Miami’s winning streak. Messi scored in the 86th minute, his eighth goal in five matches with his new club, and Inter Miami rolled past Charlotte 4-0 in a Leagues Cup quarterfinal game on Friday night.

Headline: Messi scores from a free kick to give Argentina 1-0 win in South American World Cup qualifying
Content: Lionel Messi scored from a free kick in the 78th minute to give Argentina a 1-0 win against Ecuador in the first round of South American World Cup qualifying.

Headline: FIFA defends expanded Club World Cup despite concerns over player welfare
Content: FIFA has defended its newly expanded Club World Cup from criticism that players are being overworked by pointing to the longevity of aging stars like Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo.

Headline: Messi makes shortlist for UEFA award as best player last season alongside De Bruyne and Haaland
Content: Lionel Messi has made the shortlist for the UEFA award as the best player in Europe last season. Messi has left Paris Saint-Germain to join Inter Miami.

Headline: Lionel Messi helps PSG secure record 11th French league title, breaks European scoring record
Content: Lionel Messi has helped Paris Saint-Germain clinch a record 11th French league title, and broke another scoring record in the process.

Headline: Messi sparkles again on free kick with tying goal, Inter Miami beats FC Dallas in shootout
Content: Lionel Messi scored on another mesmerizing free kick in his third consecutive two-goal game for Inter Miami.

Headline: Messi misses Argentina’s 3-0 win in Bolivia; Brazil beats Peru in World Cup qualifiers
